TV director Mat<0xC4><0x9B>j Li<0xC5><0xA1>ka and the manager of the Prague music club Marek Greger are behind the idea of using the already planned routes for the transport of consignments.
With the idea, they breathed life to three applications with different geographical reach.
We launched the national application in May.
At the moment, there are thousands of cities uploaded in it, and we will expand the network.
In the Czech Republic, we want to learn this first before we focus more on abroad, says the 41-year-old manager in an interview with iDNES.cz.
How does the app work and who can benefit from it?
You can download it and register for free.
Then you can specify the route and data, how big the package can be transported and how much you want for it.
Somebody might be asking for a ride that day.
When the route and time of delivery are suitable, it is paired and both receive mutual notification.
At that moment, a chat room opens, where the couple arranges a handover.
How many people would you estimate would have to register for each package to always find its courier?
