We see this as a success and we hope that more will be added.
Is there a risk that the sender will wait too long?
We hope to compete for large conglomerates simply because we are able to deliver the item on the same day and for a fraction of the price.
In a large company, you will pay several thousand for delivery within two hours.
You may pay a hundred or less here, because this is the path someone is already taking.
Should traditional carriers be worried about a possible loss of customers in the future?
We hope so.
The market has huge potential, huge multinational carriers feed here, as well as retail chains, where everyone started shopping and gradually found that quality does not correspond to what they pay for.
No one wants to find a note in their mailbox telling them to pick up the parcel at the branch office, first on the day after 7:00 p.m.
At that time I needed the package for six hours and I waited at home because it was important.
We want a better, faster and more functional service that does not annoy anyone and sends a signal to the competition, no matter how hard they try.
