In 2014, they began to prepare the Shippansee LTD application, which uses already scheduled trips between the world’s metropolises, especially by airplane, to transport packages.
In 2015, they commissioned a project to be processed by a company that created applications for example for MALL.cz, Jobs.cz or <0xC4><0x8C>SFD.
Programming took three quarters of a year and the application was launched in March 2016.
They started developing the Preveza app in December last year and released it in May this year.
This is a local version of Shippansee adapted for the Czech market.
They have been developing the Monthly and Monthly Profi app since January this year and made it available to users at the end of July 2016.
The intention was from the beginning to make all these applications, which one day will merge into one.
In the Czech Republic, they want to fine-tune the application and then, in cooperation with a strong investor, focus more on the global market.
The shared economy has been a topic lately, and this is a service like AirBnB or Uber.
Are you not worried about operating in an area that no one can tell you much about yet, where the boundaries of sharing are and where the grey economy is?
It's the same, just a different product.
It is clear to us that if it succeeds and we go up with it, we will be another thorn in the eye through the grey economy.
But even if someone saves and someone earns, it is not the intention to bypass tax authorities and tax controls.
Every user, on one side or the other, will be encouraged to tax their income if they make income from it.
What makes you think the service has such great potential?
The sender saves and the carrier earns or reduces the cost of the trip.
This is the strong idea that unites interest on both sides.
In the age of social media that divides people, we would like this one to bring people together.
They can create nice stories, people are happy to help someone and they will tell about it.
For example, someone will bring you forgotten glasses, keys or pills.
I think people have been missing a personal approach for a long time, we say about this application that it is a service of people to people.
So how do you make sure the courier doesn't run away with the package?
Each user of the application together with the registration scans the ID card and indicates the bank connection, payment or credit card.
These are the channels that give credibility to the service and the person.
Couriers also collect stars based on senders’ ratings.
We also offer insurance, we still fine-tune the details.
The courier is liable for uninsured shipment in case of loss or damage, but does not accept responsibility for the contents under criminal law if there is something illegal inside and does not know about it.
If he is stopped by the police and found in a sealed package in his trunk a submachine gun or ten kilos of hashish, criminal responsibility falls on the sender.
Is there a risk of misuse of sensitive data from the database?
Registered persons are, if necessary, traceable by the administrative body, which will be the only one who will have the opportunity to look into it, even we ourselves are not able to see them, the data is protected against misuse.
How much money will the courier receive after successful delivery of the parcel?
The courier determines the price and receives the full amount he asks for.
The sender will be charged a few percent extra for the mediation of the contact.
This money is our profit, but it is only a few percent, because we want to push volume.
Also, no one can accuse the courier of not delivering the parcel when it was actually delivered, both the pick-up and delivery are verified using QR codes.
Are there any limitations?
Whether in relation to the size or content of the package?
You can carry anything.
We have three sizes, small as a cube of butter, medium as a plateau of eggs and large as a bass beer.
After that, there are no more restrictions, and if someone has space in the car, they can carry a refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the app, so the courier can see what he wants.
You don’t even have to pack a thing unless you explicitly want to hide the content.
You put a forgotten hoodie in the courier's hand and that's it.
Who came up with the idea and how long did it take to start the service?
A friend had an idea more than two years ago, I didn’t pay much attention to it at the time.
Then he showed me a demo application with a transnational reach that mainly targets air passengers.
At that moment, I told him that I would not look for an investor, but I wanted to become one myself and put savings into it.
It took another year of development before we established Shippansee LTD in London to increase the credibility of the entire product.
But this is not the version you are focusing on right now.
No, we focused marketing on the Czech Republic, where we are trying to catch up on the application, because it all had birth pains and there is still something to solve and improve.
We try to respond to customer feedback and we do not deal with the foreign market as much at the moment.
We know it’s a long run, but we don’t rush, we want to create a really good product for people.
Shippansee LTD was the basic and most expensive application, the other two were in some way upgrades.
The takeover was created when we said that the national segment could be much more interesting and that we would at least learn this in the Czech Republic.
The third application of the Moon is local, for the city.
But he can send a package to the exact address and to the other end of the world.
It works for the sender as well as the carrier, but the difference is that as a courier you see the shipments in the form of points on the map that are closest to you, thanks to the geolocator in your mobile phone.
The application for couriers who want to make a living from it, we called the Month of Profi.
So someone can make a living picking up packages around town?
Exactly, the last application will be downloaded in Prague by a taxi driver, a student, a mother on parental leave, someone who wants to make a trip to work.
Now that everyone's messing with the Pokémon, they can collect this the same way.
A person sees where the orders are around the city, comes to it, clicks and sees when it must be delivered and transports the shipment.
It is set cheaper than competitive services.
At the moment, we are also creating a web interface that will be central for companies to send shipments, fill in data on the web about them, or create points on the map.
We are then able to invoice them for the use of the service every month.
Are you currently working on the full-time project?
It burdens us, but we have it normally at work, so that we can support and develop the project.
There is no strong multinational investor behind us, we are two guys, one of whom had a brilliant idea and the other jumped into it with other incentives and ideas.
Now we are looking for an investor strong enough to manage not the Czech market with us, but who should go with us to the global product and become another huge player in the market such as AirBnB and Uber.
