But I watched the whole thing.
He was out of work at 3:30, so she always left at 3:00 to go shopping.
Every day she tried to see him.
Later I found out that they were meeting at his house, in the laundry.
How many times did I know they were there?
I got the keys, he was determined to catch them there.
But I don't know why, in the end I always stayed home.
I've never been able to go there, to take that decisive step.
You may laugh at me, but I believe my wife controlled me mentally.
Soon, I think, she found out that I was controllable, that I would do whatever she wanted.
And I really did.
Maybe I'm just a slipper.
My neighbors told me they knew that too.
I was such an asshole that I never asked them what to do.
I was afraid that if it all broke up, it would be bad.
That it would happen to everyone in the family, only the daughter knew something.
So I've always put it off, on and on.
One day, I went to his apartment to ask for help in the laundry room.
He went with me, and I told him that I had gotten anonymous, that he was seeing my wife, and that it all hinted at that.
I asked him what he would say.
He stood there, shrugging his shoulders, staring down at the ground, not saying a word.
Then, too, I met his wife once on the way from the store.
I told her, but she didn't believe it at all.
She didn’t react to it and didn’t tell me anything either.
Nobody told me anything at the time.
I'm the kind of guy who's never really gone out, who has a hard time meeting someone, let alone finding a woman.
So I didn't even think about getting a divorce.
I was always hoping that one day it would end.
I figured I'd forgive her for all that, and life would go on.
It wasn't like that.
