I still have it in me to this day.
I used to show it to her quite often, but in the end I let it go for the sake of peace.
He still lives in the next house, and I still live with her.
It's just that it's more like my wife's my housekeeper.
She always did everything at home - cooking, washing, cleaning.
She's hardworking.
I always wanted to make sure I had no other reason to complain.
And she's kind, you might say.
But sometimes I want to caress her, hug her, and she won't let me.
We go for walks and shopping together, and everyone thinks about what a happy marriage we have.
But she once told me that she never loved me.
She loved me, but she didn’t love me.
And I see that she loves him to this day, he is her god.
